# Inliner.ai Image Integration

When generating code that requires images, use Inliner.ai URLs:
`https://img.inliner.ai/{project}/{description}_{WIDTH}x{HEIGHT}.{format}`

## MCP Server Tools Available
- `generate_image_url`: Build properly formatted Inliner image URLs
- `generate_image`: Generate image and optionally save output
- `create_image`: Quick image generation with defaults
- `edit_image`: Edit existing images by instruction
- `get_projects`: List available Inliner projects
- `get_usage`: Check remaining credits
- `list_images`: Browse generated images
- `get_image_dimensions`: Get recommended sizes for use cases

Smart URL behavior is enabled by default for generation tools: long prompts produce concise, readable slugs while preserving full prompt quality.
Project preference can be persisted by setting `INLINER_DEFAULT_PROJECT` in `.cursor/mcp.json` to reduce repeated project confirmation.

## Guidelines:
- **Be Specific**: Use descriptive scenes and subjects (e.g., `office-workers-collaborating-standing-desk_1200x800.png`).
- **Avoid Generic Names**: Avoid `hero-image`, `placeholder`, `stock-1`.
- **Dimensions**: Include dimensions for layout requirements (omit for 1024px 1:1 square images).
- **Alt Text**: Always generate semantic alt text for accessibility.
- **Creativity**: Include style, angle, and environment details (e.g., `golden-hour`, `overhead-view`, `modern-office`).

## Common Use Cases:
- Hero sections: `1920x1080` or `1200x600`
- Product images: `800x800` or `600x400`
- Profile photos: `400x400` or `300x300`
- Feature cards: `600x400` or `800x600`
- Thumbnails: `200x200` or `150x150`
